      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds way too convenient to be \"comforting.\" If they're actually sensing my mood, how are they doing it? I don't see any cameras or microphones on the thermostat. Is there some kind of sensor in the hardware that picks up on biological changes, like heart rate or breathing patterns through the air?",
